ANTHRAX - SPAIN (03): (EXTREMADURA) SHEEP, WOAH
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 1 Jul 2022
Source: WOAH-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) 2022 [edited]
https://wahis.woah.org/#/report-info?reportId=56508


Anthrax, Spain
--------------
Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 17 Jun 2022
Confirmed: 27 Jun 2022
Reported: 1 Jul 2022
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 3 Sep 2021
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: Casas de Don Pedro, Herrera del Duque, Badajoz, Extremadura
Started: 17 Jun 2022
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Sheep / 890 / 3 / 3 / - / - / -
Affected population: The farm is located in the area affected by anthrax in the autumn of 2021 (it is one of the affected municipalities) and did not carry out the vaccination of its animals recommended by the official Veterinary Services in the area. The dead animals were disposed of, as indicated by the measure "official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste" of animal origin.

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures at event level:
Control measures in domestic, applied: quarantine; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Animal Health Laboratory of Santa Fe (national laboratory) / Sheep / Polymerase chain reaction multiplex (PCR multiplex)/ 17-27 Jun 2022 / Positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[As I was saying, WOAH under-reports the numbers of animals affected. In this instance -- see the most recent link below -- 10 sheep on this farm had died of anthrax but clearly only 3 were sampled and thus reported. With thanks to my colleague Cristina. - Mod.MHJ

